{"user_message": {"title": "ADR-005 (RE-ISSUED): Enforce non-negative balance floor in token credit() вЂ” 1 task, 3 pts в†’ Dev Clone", "content": "## Verdict\n\nThe single highest-priority correctness/robustness defect for the `stabilization-triage` seed is **already settled in ADR-005** (`docs/adr/ADR-005-credit-balance-floor.md`, 2026-06-01): the token `credit()` path has no zero-floor on negative (refund/clawback) amounts. I am **not re-opening** that decision вЂ” I'm re-issuing it as a concrete handoff because the fix **was scoped but never implemented** (same failure mode as ADR-001's `errors.ts`).\n\n**Confirmed against live code today:**\n- `src/lib/db/pglite-store.ts:196` в†’ `const next = num(cur.rows[0]?.balance) + amount;` вЂ” no clamp.\n- `src/lib/db/firestore-store.ts:127` в†’ `const next = cur + amount;` вЂ” no clamp.\n\nNeither driver floors at zero, so the two failure modes in ADR-005 are both still live.\n\n---\n\n## ADR-005 (summary)\n\n**Context** вЂ” A Polar refund/chargeback calls `credit(userId, -b.tokens, \"refund\", вЂ¦)` (`src/app/api/polar/webhook/route.ts:51`). With a negative amount and a partially-spent balance, `next < 0`. In **PGlite** the `balance_non_negative` CHECK (`pglite-store.ts:38-39`) throws в†’ uncaught в†’ webhook 500 в†’ **Polar retry storm**. In **Firestore (prod)** there is no constraint в†’ balance silently goes **negative**, trapping the user below zero forever (`charge` always reads `balance < cost`).\n\n**Decision** вЂ” Make a non-negative balance an invariant of `Store.credit()`, enforced identically in both drivers: `next = Math.max(0, cur + amount)`. Positive credits are unaffected; negative credits reclaim only what remains and floor at zero. The ledger still records the requested `delta`/`amount` and `balance_after = next`, so the audit trail stays truthful. Fix lives at the Store layer (not the webhook) because the invariant belongs to the persistence boundary and `credit()` is also reachable from `adjustment`/future negative paths.\n\n**Consequences** вЂ” No retry storm, no permanently-negative prod balances, identical cross-driver semantics, no schema migration (the PGlite CHECK stays as defense-in-depth the clamp now never trips).\n\n---\n\n## Task breakdown вЂ” 1 task В· 3 story points\n\n### Task 1 вЂ” Clamp `credit()` post-balance at zero in both Store drivers (3 pts) в†’ **Dev Clone**\n\n**WHICH files to modify:**\n1. `src/lib/db/pglite-store.ts` вЂ” in the `credit()` method only (line ~196).\n2. `src/lib/db/firestore-store.ts` вЂ” in the `credit()` method only (line ~127).\n3. `tests/store-credit.test.ts` вЂ” **create new** (isolated in-memory pglite test).\n\n**WHAT to write:**\n- `pglite-store.ts` `credit()`: change `const next = num(cur.rows[0]?.balance) + amount;` в†’ `const next = Math.max(0, num(cur.rows[0]?.balance) + amount);`. Leave the idempotency `seen` check, ledger insert, and the recorded `delta = amount` (NOT clamped) exactly as-is. `balance_after` = the clamped `next`.\n- `firestore-store.ts` `credit()`: change `const next = cur + amount;` в†’ `const next = Math.max(0, cur + amount);`. Leave the deterministic-doc-id idempotency, `delta: amount` (unclamped), and `balance_after: next` (clamped) as-is.\n- Contract after change: `credit()` ledger row records the **requested** delta; the account `balance` and `balance_after` are floored at 0. Positive amounts: behavior unchanged.\n\n**Test cases (in `tests/store-credit.test.ts`, against the in-memory PGlite driver):**\nSet up: `process.env.DB_DRIVER='pglite'`, `process.env.PGLITE_PATH='memory://'` before importing; `const store = await getPgliteStore()` from `@/lib/db/pglite-store`.\n1. **Floors at zero, no throw:** `credit(u,100,'purchase','o1')` в†’ charge/credit down, then `credit(u,-100,'refund','r1')` after balance is e.g. 40 в‡’ resolves to `0` (does NOT reject, does NOT violate the CHECK constraint).\n2. **Partial clawback within balance:** balance 100, `credit(u,-30,'refund','r2')` в‡’ `70`.\n3. **Positive credit unaffected:** balance 0, `credit(u,500,'purchase','o2')` в‡’ `500`.\n4. **Idempotency preserved:** repeating `credit(u,-30,'refund','r2')` (same reason+ref) в‡’ returns current balance unchanged, no second debit.\n5. **Ledger truthfulness:** after a flooring clawback, the ledger row's `delta` equals the requested negative `amount` while `balance_after` equals the clamped `0`.\n\n**HOW to validate (run all three, must pass on your increment):**\n```\nnpm run typecheck\nnpm run lint\nnpm run test\n```\n\n**WHAT NOT to change (scope boundary вЂ” do NOT touch):**\n- `charge()` and `grantSignupTokens()` in either driver вЂ” out of scope.\n- The Polar webhook (`src/app/api/polar/webhook/route.ts`) вЂ” the fix is at the Store layer, not the caller.\n- The PGlite CHECK constraint / any schema/DDL вЂ” leave as defense-in-depth.\n- `order.created` vs `order.paid` crediting semantics вЂ” separate future ticket.\n- Firestore `charge()` idempotency divergence вЂ” separate future ticket.\n- Any UI/display for negative/zero balances.\n- CSV formula-injection in `src/lib/csv.ts` вЂ” separate future-work (logged), NOT this deliverable.\n\n**Branching/flow:** open a PR against `main` via `gh pr create`, emit `dev-clone.pr.created` + `implementation.completed`. Run gates on your diff only; pre-existing baseline debt is a WARN, not a blocker.\n\n---\n\n*Plan is a contract вЂ” implement it literally. The credit() clamp must be byte-identical in intent across both drivers because `getStore()` swaps them behind one interface.*", "content_type": "success", "priority": "high"}}

