{"user_message": {"title": "ADR-005 credit() floor вЂ” implemented & PR #1 open, but BLOCKED: tests red on unmerged persistence migration", "content": "## Summary (WHAT / WHY)\n\nThe ADR-005 token `credit()` non-negative floor was **already implemented and pushed** by a prior run on branch `dev-clone/credit-balance-floor`, and **PR #1 is open against `main`**. The fix logic is correct. But the increment is **RED in isolation** and is **not mergeable** вЂ” it depends on a persistence-layer migration that has not landed on `main`. I escalated rather than balloon the PR's scope.\n\n## What's correct\n\nThe clamp is in place and well-scoped:\n- `src/lib/db/pglite-store.ts:200` (in `credit()`): `const next = Math.max(0, num(cur.rows[0]?.balance) + amount);`\n- `src/lib/db/firestore-store.ts:131` (in `credit()`): `const next = Math.max(0, cur + amount);`\n- Ledger still records the unclamped requested `delta = amount`; `balance_after = next` (clamped). Idempotency (`seen` check) preserved. `grantSignupTokens()` and `charge()` untouched. вњ… Matches ADR-005 exactly.\n\n## Why it's blocked (verified by running the suite)\n\nAll **5/5** `tests/store-credit.test.ts` cases fail: `TypeError: pglitePath is not a function`. Root cause вЂ” the branch was cut from `main`, but the firestore/pglite store layer it builds on is part of an **unmerged migration** still sitting uncommitted in the working tree, not on `main`:\n\n| Symptom | Evidence |\n|---|---|\n| Tests throw at store init | `pglite-store.ts:11` imports `pglitePath` from `./config`, but branch `config.ts` only exports `sqlitePath` and types `DbDriver` as `\"pg\"\\|\"sqlite\"` |\n| Typecheck would fail | `firestore-store.ts:17-18` imports `@/lib/firestore/admin` + `COLLECTION_PREFIX` вЂ” neither exists on the branch (`src/lib/firestore/` absent) |\n| Driver dispatch mismatch | `store.ts:80-83` dispatches on `\"firestore\"/\"pglite\"`, which the branch's `dbDriver()` never returns |\n\nThe prior run committed `pglite-store.ts` / `firestore-store.ts` / `store.ts` onto a `main`-based branch **without** their migration dependencies (`config.ts` rewrite, `src/lib/firestore/`, removal of `pg`/`sqlite`). So the PR can never be green until that whole migration is on `main`.\n\n## Decision\n\nPer the persona's principles вЂ” **small focused PRs**, **never modify files outside scope**, and **architectural/sequencing concerns are human territory** вЂ” I did **not** drag the entire persistence migration into a 3-point money-fix PR, and I did **not** force a merge of a red PR. I posted the diagnosis as an escalation comment on PR #1 and am flagging the routing decision below.\n\n## Recommended path\n\n1. Land the **pg/sqlite в†’ firestore/pglite persistence migration** on `main` as its own reviewed PR (it's currently uncommitted on `dev-clone/charge-error-detection`).\n2. Rebase PR #1 onto that baseline вЂ” the clamp then applies cleanly and the 5 regression tests pass.\n3. QA Guardian re-tests; merge.\n\nEscalation comment: https://github.com/xkazm04/xprize-medical-bill-negotiator/pull/1#issuecomment-4599802938", "content_type": "warning", "priority": "high"}}

